It appears you have a merge in progress. To undo all changes, including the merge, I recommend aborting the merge first.

I will use `git merge --abort` to stop the current merge and revert to the state before the merge attempt. This will discard any changes made during the merge process.

After

that, if there are still uncommitted changes, I will use `git reset --hard HEAD` to discard them and revert your working directory to the last committed state. This is a destructive operation and will permanently delete any uncommitted changes.

Do you want to proceed with `git merge --abort`?
